The PagePickerAction stores the SearchQueryBean in the session. This is bad for two reasons:

1) The SearchQueryBean is not fully serializable, and will therefore cause errors if the session is serialized by the app server
2) Parameters like that should be transfered to the next page using get/post parameters, instead of cluttering the session with data that is never cleared.

