When using the widget connector to link to e.g. Youtube videos, the format required is currently

{code}
{widget:url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WPlbsF1fo2E&NR=1}
{code}

As there is only one parameter needed, the url, it should be possible to just pass in the value, and not need to specify the 'url='.  This would be consistent with how other macros work.

{code}
{widget:http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WPlbsF1fo2E&NR=1}
